Post.title: Hello World
Post._content:
Welcome to [Hexo](https://hexo.io/)! This is your very first post. Check [documentation](https://hexo.io/docs/) for more info. If you get any problems when using Hexo, you can find the answer in [troubleshooting](https://hexo.io/docs/troubleshooting.html) or you can ask me on [GitHub](https://github.com/hexojs/hexo/issues).

## Quick Start

### Create a new post

``` bash
$ hexo new "My New Post"
```

More info: [Writing](https://hexo.io/docs/writing.html)

### Run server

``` bash
$ hexo server
```

More info: [Server](https://hexo.io/docs/server.html)

### Generate static files

``` bash
$ hexo generate
```

More info: [Generating](https://hexo.io/docs/generating.html)

### Deploy to remote sites

``` bash
$ hexo deploy
```

More info: [Deployment](https://hexo.io/docs/one-command-deployment.html)

``` bash
 npm install
---
```

Post.title: Linux.md
Post._content:
## Linux
- 
```bash
[root@localhost _posts]# lsof -i:8888
bash: lsof: 
[root@localhost _posts]# yum install lsof
.....

[root@localhost _posts]# lsof -i:8888
COMMAND   PID USER   FD   TYPE  DEVICE SIZE/OFF NODE NAME
node    47161 root   20u  IPv6 1354694      0t0  TCP *:ddi-tcp-1 (LISTEN)
[root@localhost _posts]# kill -9 47161
[root@localhost _posts]# lsof -i:8888
[6]+                 hexo s
```

Post.title: git
Post._content:
## git
> git pushdefaultgitpush
> Git2.0push.default'matching'2.0'simple'
> push.defaultnothing , current , upstream , simple , matching

### push.default 
- nothing : eg : git push origin branchname
- current :  push
- upstream : pushupstream
- simple : upstreamsimpleupstreampush
- matching : push

###  push.default
```bash
git config --global push.default current
```
